Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement_list
Rule 2     statement_list -> statement_list statement
Rule 3     statement_list -> statement
Rule 4     statement -> LET IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression
Rule 5     statement -> PRINT LPAREN expression RPAREN
Rule 6     expression -> expression PLUS expression
Rule 7     expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 8     expression -> expression MULTIPLY expression
Rule 9     expression -> expression DIVIDE expression
Rule 10    expression -> INTEGER
Rule 11    expression -> IDENTIFIER
Rule 12    expression -> LPAREN expression RPAREN

Terminals, with rules where they appear

ASSIGN               : 4
DIVIDE               : 9
IDENTIFIER           : 4 11
INTEGER              : 10
LET                  : 4
LPAREN               : 5 12
MINUS                : 7
MULTIPLY             : 8
PLUS                 : 6
PRINT                : 5
RPAREN               : 5 12
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

expression           : 4 5 6 6 7 7 8 8 9 9 12
program              : 0
statement            : 2 3
statement_list       : 1 2

Parsing method: LALR

